# .easignore — overrides .gitignore for EAS Build uploads only.
#
# EAS Build uses .gitignore by default to decide what to upload to the
# build worker (https://docs.expo.dev/build-reference/easignore/). The
# .gitignore rule for `google-services.json` (round 5 fix on PR #885)
# is there to prevent accidental `git add` of the real Firebase config
# locally — but EAS legitimately needs that file in the upload so the
# Android build can compile against it. Mirror .gitignore here, minus
# the Firebase line, so EAS gets google-services.json (placeholder or
# swapped real config) while local git stays protected.
#
# Keep this file in sync with .gitignore manually — they cover the same
# build-exclusion set except for the Firebase line.

# dependencies
node_modules/

# Expo
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
expo-env.d.ts

# Native
.kotlin/
*.orig.*
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision

# Metro
.metro-health-check*

# debug
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*

# macOS
.DS_Store
*.pem

# local env files
.env*.local

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo

# generated native folders
/ios
/android

# Jest coverage (N4)
coverage/

# google-services.json is intentionally NOT excluded here so EAS Build
# can package whichever config (placeholder or real) is on disk at
# build time. .gitignore still blocks accidental local commits of the
# real config.
